-- Hong Kong Developer Wins Approval for London City Hotel
-- B y   P a t r i c k   G o w e r
-- 2013-11-05T11:54:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-05/hong-kong-developer-wins-approval-for-london-city-hotel.html
A 275-bedroom hotel on the edge of
the City of  London  financial district to be built by Hong Kong-based developer  Dorsett Hospitality International Ltd. (2266)  won
local-government approval.  City of London officials granted planning permission for
the hotel at a meeting today. The project includes the
demolition of an existing 1970s office building and the
construction of the 13-story hotel, according to a filing.  Dorsett is a unit of Far East Consortium International Ltd.
The City of London hotel is one of two properties Dorsett is
developing in the U.K., according to the companyâ€™s  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
